},\"url\":\"https://assets.genius.com/images/default_avatar_16.png?1726687620\"}},\"apiPath\":\"/users/11307091\",\"aboutMeSummary\":\"\",\"type\":\"user\"}},\"comments\":{\"8026596\":{\"reason\":null,\"author\":11307091,\"anonymousAuthor\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"accept\",\"reject\",\"mark_spam\",\"integrate\",\"archive\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":7,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"id\":8026596,\"hasVoters\":true,\"createdAt\":1600421024,\"commentableType\":\"Annotation\",\"commentableId\":3690688,\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"I love this song you can\'t diss this song like come on it\'s the back street boys for crying out loud\",\"html\":\"<p>I love this song you can’t diss this song like come on it’s the back street boys for crying out loud<\/p>\"},\"apiPath\":\"/comments/8026596\",\"type\":\"comment\"}},\"annotations\":{\"3690688\":{\"verifiedBy\":null,\"topComment\":8026596,\"rejectionComment\":null,\"createdBy\":11524,\"cosignedBy\":[],\"authors\":[{\"user\":2197748,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.6687116564417178,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":11524,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.2822085889570552,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":263424,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.046012269938650305,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":6353121,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.003067484662576687,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"acceptedBy\":7,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"iqByAction\":{},\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null,\"pyong\":false,\"cosign\":false},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"cosign\",\"uncosign\",\"destroy\",\"accept\",\"reject\",\"see_unreviewed\",\"clear_votes\",\"propose_edit_to\",\"pin_to_profile\",\"unpin_from_profile\",\"update_source\",\"edit_custom_preview\",\"create_comment\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":71,\"verified\":false,\"url\":\"https://genius.com/3690688/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way/I-want-it-that-way\",\"twitterShareMessage\":\"““I Want It That Way” is about a strained relationship. The lyrical interpretation of this song, however,…” —@Genius\",\"state\":\"accepted\",\"source\":null,\"shareUrl\":\"https://genius.com/3690688\",\"referentId\":3690688,\"pyongsCount\":null,\"proposedEditCount\":0,\"pinned\":false,\"needsExegesis\":false,\"id\":3690688,\"hasVoters\":true,\"embedContent\":\"<blockquote class=\'rg_standalone_container\' data-src=\'//genius.com/annotations/3690688/standalone_embed\'><a href=\'https://genius.com/3690688/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way/I-want-it-that-way\'>I Want It That Way<\/a><br><a href=\'https://genius.com/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-lyrics\'>&#8213; Backstreet Boys – I Want It That Way<\/a><\/blockquote><script async crossorigin src=\'//genius.com/annotations/load_standalone_embeds.js\'><\/script>\",\"deleted\":false,\"customPreview\":null,\"createdAt\":1403713763,\"community\":true,\"commentCount\":4,\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"\\\"I Want It That Way\\\" is about a strained relationship. The lyrical interpretation of this song, however, is notoriously muddled. They don\'t necessarily make sense—and this is the subject of much the [online discussion](http://www.laweekly.com/music/what-the-hell-is-backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-about-update-mind-blowing-shit-has-come-to-light-2411586#page-2) about this song. The lyrics were written by Max Martin and Andreas Carlsson, veteran Swedish hitmakers that began their careers at Cheiron Studios, which was [largely responsible for the sound of pop](http://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/blank-space-what-kind-of-genius-is-max-martin) in the ’90s. Carlsson talked to [HitQuarters](http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_Andreas_Carlsson_Interview.html) about writing this song:\\n\\n>‘I Want It That Way’ was a play with words. When Max came up with the original idea for the song, it already had the line \'you are my fire, the one desire.\' We tried a million different variations on the second verse, and finally we had to go back to what was sounding so great, \'you are my fire, the one desire.\' And then we changed it to \'am I your fire, your one desire,\' which made absolutely no sense in combination with the chorus - but everybody loved it!\\n\\nThe song\'s guitar riff was inspired by Metallica. There was an alternate version of the song recorded with more coherent lyrics, but the band preferred the original version of the song. Backstreet Boy Kevin Richardson said that Martin\'s English language skills were worse then, which is why the song\'s lyrics don\'t make a ton of sense. He told [*LA Weekly*](http://www.popdust.com/backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-lyrics-analysis-which-way-is-it-exa-1889572029.html):\\n\\n>Ultimately the song really doesn\'t really make much sense.\\n\\nThe video for this song, which was parodied by [Blink-182](/Blink-182-all-the-small-things-lyrics), won a VMA for \\\"Viewer\'s Choice.\\\"\\n\\nIt was nominated for 3 Grammys in 2000: \\\"Song of the Year,\\\" \\\"Record of the Year,\\\" and \\\"Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals.\\\"\\n\\nOn August 19, 2011, China\'s Ministry of Culture [released a list of 100 songs](http://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/24/banned-china-lady-gaga-perry), including this song, that were required to be removed from the Internet as they had been released without being subjected to a mandatory screening process conducted by Ministry officials.\",\"html\":\"<p>“I Want It That Way” is about a strained relationship. The lyrical interpretation of this song, however, is notoriously muddled. They don’t necessarily make sense—and this is the subject of much the <a href=\\\"http://www.laweekly.com/music/what-the-hell-is-backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-about-update-mind-blowing-shit-has-come-to-light-2411586#page-2\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">online discussion<\/a> about this song. The lyrics were written by Max Martin and Andreas Carlsson, veteran Swedish hitmakers that began their careers at Cheiron Studios, which was <a href=\\\"http://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/blank-space-what-kind-of-genius-is-max-martin\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">largely responsible for the sound of pop<\/a> in the ’90s. Carlsson talked to <a href=\\\"http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_Andreas_Carlsson_Interview.html\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">HitQuarters<\/a> about writing this song:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>‘I Want It That Way’ was a play with words. When Max came up with the original idea for the song, it already had the line ‘you are my fire, the one desire.’ We tried a million different variations on the second verse, and finally we had to go back to what was sounding so great, ‘you are my fire, the one desire.’ And then we changed it to ‘am I your fire, your one desire,’ which made absolutely no sense in combination with the chorus – but everybody loved it!<\/p><\/blockquote>\\n\\n<p>The song’s guitar riff was inspired by Metallica. There was an alternate version of the song recorded with more coherent lyrics, but the band preferred the original version of the song. Backstreet Boy Kevin Richardson said that Martin’s English language skills were worse then, which is why the song’s lyrics don’t make a ton of sense. He told <a href=\\\"http://www.popdust.com/backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-lyrics-analysis-which-way-is-it-exa-1889572029.html\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\"><em>LA Weekly<\/em><\/a>:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>Ultimately the song really doesn’t really make much sense.<\/p><\/blockquote>\\n\\n<p>The video for this song, which was parodied by <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/Blink-182-all-the-small-things-lyrics\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/songs/62154\\\">Blink-182<\/a>, won a VMA for “Viewer’s Choice.”<\/p>\\n\\n<p>It was nominated for 3 Grammys in 2000: “Song of the Year,” “Record of the Year,” and “Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals.”<\/p>\\n\\n<p>On August 19, 2011, China’s Ministry of Culture <a href=\\\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/24/banned-china-lady-gaga-perry\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">released a list of 100 songs<\/a>, including this song, that were required to be removed from the Internet as they had been released without being subjected to a mandatory screening process conducted by Ministry officials.<\/p>\"},\"beingCreated\":false,\"apiPath\":\"/annotations/3690688\",\"type\":\"annotation\"}},\"referents\":{\"3332006\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":3332006},\"3332013\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":3332013},\"3351805\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":3351805},\"3690688\":{\"annotations\":[3690688],\"annotatable\":{\"url\":\"https://genius.com/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-lyrics\",\"type\":\"song\",\"title\":\"I Want It That Way\",\"linkTitle\":\"I Want It That Way by Backstreet Boys\",\"imageUrl\":\"https://images.genius.com/8ee8970f7def8832fd40b2cac5d47289.1000x857x1.jpg\",\"id\":105083,\"context\":\"Backstreet Boys\",\"clientTimestamps\":{\"lyricsUpdatedAt\":1725772036,\"updatedByHumanAt\":1725772044},\"apiPath\":\"/songs/105083\"},\"twitterShareMessage\":\"““I Want It That Way” is about a strained relationship. The lyrical interpretation of this song, …” —@Genius\",\"trackingPaths\":{\"concurrent\":\"/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way-lyrics\",\"aggregate\":\"/3690688/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way/I-want-it-that-way\"},\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"relationships\":{},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"add_pinned_annotation_to\",\"add_community_annotation_to\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"verifiedAnnotatorIds\":[],\"url\":\"https://genius.com/3690688/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way/I-want-it-that-way\",\"songId\":105083,\"range\":{\"content\":\"I Want It That Way\"},\"path\":\"/3690688/Backstreet-boys-i-want-it-that-way/I-want-it-that-way\",\"isImage\":false,\"isDescription\":true,\"iosAppUrl\":\"genius://referents/3690688\",\"id\":3690688,\"fragment\":\"I Want It That Way\",\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"apiPath\":\"/referents/3690688\",\"annotatorLogin\":\"tomi\",\"annotatorId\":11524,\"type\":\"referent\"},\"4892365\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":4892365},\"4892398\":{\"classification\":\"accepted\",\"editorialState\":\"accepted\",\"id\":4892398},\"21601299\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":21601299},\"21601324\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":21601324},\"28269662\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":28269662},\"29468023\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":29468023},\"30508167\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":30508167},\"30508173\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":30508173},\"30508193\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":30508193},\"30508196\":{\"classification\":\"unreviewed\",\"editorialState\":\"pending\",\"id\":30508196}},\"stubhubArtists\":{\"198\":{\"artist\":8415,\"stubhubUrl\":\"https://www.stubhub.com/backstreet-boys-tickets/performer/429\",\"stubhubId\":10234,\"minConcertTicketPriceForDisplay\":\"\$217\",\"id\":198,\"type\":\"stubhub_artist\"}},\"answers\":{\"859\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":85148,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":12,\"id\":859,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1468615830,\"bodyForEdit\":\"Voted #3 on VH1\'s list of [greatest songs from the 1990s](http://www.stereogum.com/7468/vh1s_greatest_songs_of_the_90s_not_enough_pavement/franchises/list/)\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"Voted #3 on VH1\'s list of [greatest songs from the 1990s](http://www.stereogum.com/7468/vh1s_greatest_songs_of_the_90s_not_enough_pavement/franchises/list/)\",\"html\":\"<p>Voted #3 on VH1’s list of <a href=\\\"http://www.stereogum.com/7468/vh1s_greatest_songs_of_the_90s_not_enough_pavement/franchises/list/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">greatest songs from the 1990s<\/a><\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"165438\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":4274810,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":11,\"id\":165438,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1546025374,\"bodyForEdit\":\"Andreas Carlsson ascribed the lyrics to Max Martin\'s poor English skills at the time:\\n\\n>[The lyrics to the verse] made absolutely no sense in combination with the chorus. Ultimately, the song doesn\'t really make sense.\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"Andreas Carlsson ascribed the lyrics to Max Martin\'s poor English skills at the time:\\n\\n>[The lyrics to the verse] made absolutely no sense in combination with the chorus. Ultimately, the song doesn\'t really make sense.\",\"html\":\"<p>Andreas Carlsson ascribed the lyrics to Max Martin’s poor English skills at the time:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>[The lyrics to the verse] made absolutely no sense in combination with the chorus. Ultimately, the song doesn’t really make sense.<\/p><\/blockquote>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"200142\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":3499648,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":5,\"id\":200142,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1558157830,\"bodyForEdit\":\"The song [sold](https://youtu.be/mAGGPgxl6qU?t=33) an estimated 30 million copies worldwide.\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"The song [sold](https://youtu.be/mAGGPgxl6qU?t=33) an estimated 30 million copies worldwide.\",\"html\":\"<p>The song <a href=\\\"https://youtu.be/mAGGPgxl6qU?t=33\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">sold<\/a> an estimated 30 million copies worldwide.<\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"200143\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":3499648,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":1,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":8,\"id\":200143,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1558157901,\"bodyForEdit\":\"Nick Carter:\\n>After filming the video, everyone thought we had our own airplane...we\'ve always flown commercial!\\n\\nAJ:\\n>I always loved the blink-182 parody of this video.\\n\\nKevin:\\n>We originally weren\'t supposed to do any dancing at all. At the last minute, we learned a few steps, and thought it looked really cheesy.\\n\\nHowie:\\n>We still see some of these fans in this video at our shows to this day!\\n\\nVia [YouTube](https://youtu.be/mAGGPgxl6qU)\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"Nick Carter:\\n>After filming the video, everyone thought we had our own airplane...we\'ve always flown commercial!\\n\\nAJ:\\n>I always loved the blink-182 parody of this video.\\n\\nKevin:\\n>We originally weren\'t supposed to do any dancing at all. At the last minute, we learned a few steps, and thought it looked really cheesy.\\n\\nHowie:\\n>We still see some of these fans in this video at our shows to this day!\\n\\nVia [YouTube](https://youtu.be/mAGGPgxl6qU)\",\"html\":\"<p>Nick Carter:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockquote><p>After filming the video, everyone thought we had our own airplane…we’ve always flown commercial!<\/p><\/blockquote>\\n\\n<p>AJ:<\/p>\\n\\n<blockq